# Walkthrough: Chat Improvements & Fixes

## 1. Real-time and Persistent Read Ticks (Blue Ticks)

The issue was that read receipts (double blue ticks) were not showing persistently (e.g. after refreshing the page or reloading a chat), and were not initialized on sent/received messages at runtime. 

### Cause of the Bug
- **Missing database query select:** The SQL query in [getMessages](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/mokapen/app/Http/Controllers/API/ChatController.php#L239) did not select whether messages were read (`is_read`), so all messages fetched initially or upon refresh defaulted to `is_read = undefined` (rendering single gray ticks).
- **Missing payload property:** The message sending endpoint did not return `is_read = 0` in the payload of newly sent messages, causing them to lack read status until a real-time event was received.

### Changes Made
- **Backend ([ChatController.php](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/mokapen/app/Http/Controllers/API/ChatController.php)):**
  - Added an `is_read` subquery inside the SQL statement of [getMessages](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/mokapen/app/Http/Controllers/API/ChatController.php#L239). The subquery checks if there is any other participant in the thread, and confirms that all other participants have read the message (i.e. `last_read >= created_at`). This ensures proper group and direct chat tick states.
  - Set `'is_read' => 0` in the payload for [sendMessage](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/mokapen/app/Http/Controllers/API/ChatController.php#L364).
- **Frontend ([MessageThread.jsx](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/Internal-chat-crm/src/components/Chat/MessageThread.jsx)):**
  - Added `is_read: 0` to the temporary message object created immediately when sending.
  - Added `is_read: data.is_read ?? 0` inside the `.message.sent` Echo listener.

