## 2. Push Notification Error: [VAPID] You must provide a public key

The issue was that sometimes push notifications failed with `local.ERROR: Push notification error: [VAPID] You must provide a public key.`, even though keys were configured in `.env`.

### Cause of the Bug
- In Laravel, when configuration caching is enabled (e.g., `php artisan config:cache` has been executed), accessing environment variables directly using the `env()` helper outside of configuration files returns `null`.
- [PushController.php](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/mokapen/app/Http/Controllers/API/PushController.php) was using `env('VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY')`, etc., directly in the controller instead of using the `config()` helper, which resulted in `null` values after config caching.

### Changes Made
- **Backend ([PushController.php](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/mokapen/app/Http/Controllers/API/PushController.php)):**
  - Replaced all calls to `env('VAPID_...')` with the corresponding config variables defined in [config/webpush.php](file:///c:/xampp7.4/htdocs/mokapen/config/webpush.php) (using `config('webpush.vapid.public_key')`, `config('webpush.vapid.subject')`, and `config('webpush.vapid.private_key')`).
- Cleared the configuration cache using `php artisan config:clear`.
